{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Since GPT-4V was not asked to detect malignancy in the prompt, we covert its differential diagnosis outputs into binary labels of malignancy or not.",
    "For the comparison, we use the top-3 predictions and threshold it at 0.5 for both dermatologists and GPT-4V.",
    "We use the accuracy, sensitivity, precision, and F1-scores for comparison.",
    "For diagnostic performance and malignancy detection, 95% confidence intervals are generated by bootstrapping 1000 times, and p-values through the chi-squared test.",
    "DatasetWe use the Visual USMLE [10] dataset for evaluating GPT-4V's capabilities on general medicine question answering."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "DatasetWe use the Visual USMLE [10] dataset for evaluating GPT-4V's capabilities on general medicine question answering."
  ]
}